# Conventional Commits

Follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) for every commit message in this repo.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]
```

- **type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- **scope** (optional): area of change, e.g. `bracket`, `export`, `teams`
- **description** (required): imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period, max ~72 chars
- **body** (optional): explain *why*, not *what*; wrap at 72 chars

## Type guide

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| `feat` | New user-facing capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | README or documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting, no logic change |
| `refactor` | Code change, no feature or fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `build` | Build system or dependencies |
| `ci` | CI/CD workflows |
| `chore` | Maintenance, tooling, misc |

## Examples

```
feat(export): capture full bracket content in PNG download

fix(ui): align knockout instruction text with stage header

docs: regenerate README for current project state

ci: add GitHub Pages deployment workflow

refactor(data): move teams and flags into teams.json
```

## Breaking changes

Add `!` after type/scope or a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer:

```
feat(bracket)!: remove share URL encoding from UI
```
